JOS  – Commander Operation Safe Haven Major General Ibrahim Ali has announced the release of kidnapped Plateau monarch Charles Mato from the den of his abductors in the early hours of Friday morning. In a statement on Friday morning in Jos through STF spokesman, Major Takwa and made available to Saturday Independent, said while the paramount ruler of Gindiri in Mangu Local Government Area of Plateau State, Chief Charles Mato has been with his abductors, the Commander Op­eration SAFE HAVEN Major General Ibrahim Ali placed the troops deployed at Gyanbus on red alert and a hot trail of the perpetrators. Major Takwa said conse­quently, eight suspects were arrested in connection with the kidnap incidence and in­terrogated. ADREX Properties Boss, David Onuh Receives Apple Bite’s Real… We Won’t Tolerate Defaulters Of Speed Limit Devices In 2022 –… “Following this develop­ment, the paramount ruler early this morning of Friday 31 December 2021 was released by his abductors.” He added that Operations SAFE HAVEN is still very much on the ground to ensure all those involved in the kidnap of the traditional ruler are ar­rested and made to face the full wrath of the law.